<h2>Zoological Garden in Dhaka</h2>
<p>
  <img src="/img/dest_reviews/ZooDakha.JPG" alt="Zoological Garden in Dhaka" align="left" width="432" height="345"/>
  Zoological Garden in Dhaka is one of the best places to visit in the city. The tourists who decide to set out for Dhaka Tours should definitely visit the Zoological Garden in Dhaka. The location of the Zoological Garden in Dhaka is in an advantageous position and since the city of Dhaka is connected by a good transportation network the tourists manage to reach the place easily. The Zoological Garden in Dhaka is also referred to as the Mirpur Zoo. The garden can be accessed by traveling a distance of 16 kilometers from the city center of Dhaka. The Zoological Garden in Dhaka is quite spacious indeed and is spread over an area of 205 acres. The garden attracts a considerable number of tourists all the year round and has an enormous collection of animal's species.<br>
The Zoological Garden in Dhaka presents an overwhelming collection of 150 birds and animals which varies from being 128 species in all. The animals which are found in the garden ranges from monkeys, panthers, deer, crocodiles and tigers, giraffe and tapirs to name a few.
 
